ed organizational strategies for legal study.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aFachdidaktik /Recht. 4aJuristisches Studium /Recht. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh  aTeaching methodology/Law.  alegal studies/Law.1 aLohse, Eva Julia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSchmid, Matthias, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2014z9783110370232oZDB-23-DGC0 cEPUBz97831103740180 cprintz978311031236240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311031243040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110312430423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110312430/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGCb2014  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-GLAc2000d2014